WEBVTT

1
00:01:46.745 --> 00:01:48.264
You're special.

2
00:01:49.504 --> 00:01:52.984
You have a very special
purpose in life.

3
00:01:55.183 --> 00:01:56.584
You've been chosen.

4
00:02:07.581 --> 00:02:09.942
The Island awaits you.

5
00:02:57.973 --> 00:03:00.734
I'm fine, I'm fine, I'm fine.

6
00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:29.530
Good morning, Tower One.

7
00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:33.047
Exterior contamination index
is 85 percent.

8
00:03:33.127 --> 00:03:34.528
Sunny and mild.

9
00:03:45.206 --> 00:03:47.126
Hey, I'm missing a left shoe.

10
00:03:50.526 --> 00:03:53.286
And when you get a chance,
I'd like another color.

11
00:04:03.723 --> 00:04:06.083
- Morning.
- Good morning.

12
00:04:13.762 --> 00:04:16.842
- Hey, Lincoln. How you doing?
- I'm missing a shoe.

13
00:04:26.839 --> 00:04:29.521
- Hey, you're cutting.
- Yeah.

14
00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:32.239
Thank you.

15
00:04:33.318 --> 00:04:35.079
We're full.

16
00:04:38.118 --> 00:04:41.638
Good morning.
July 19th, 2019.

17
00:04:41.718 --> 00:04:43.878
Another day in paradise.

18
00:04:57.195 --> 00:04:59.355
Starkweather Two Delta,

19
00:04:59.395 --> 00:05:00.714
your time has come.

20
00:05:00.794 --> 00:05:03.634
You're moving out to the Island.

21
00:05:03.714 --> 00:05:05.593
Starkweather Two Delta here.

22
00:05:05.633 --> 00:05:08.913
And, as you know, the biggest dream
of my life just came true.

23
00:05:08.993 --> 00:05:11.593
I've only been with you guys
for, like, six months,

24
00:05:11.673 --> 00:05:13.353
but I won the lottery.

25
00:05:13.433 --> 00:05:15.951
- That's right, me, Starkweather, OK?
- Six months.

26
00:05:16.031 --> 00:05:20.312
To go out and breathe fresh air,
swim in the ocean...

27
00:05:20.432 --> 00:05:24.391
I can't believe I won.
You call me Mr. Popular, I know.

28
00:05:24.511 --> 00:05:27.030
It's me. It's me.

29
00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:31.550
You guys know I'm not like this,
but this is just amazing.

30
00:05:32.349 --> 00:05:34.949
I'm going to the Island!
We're gonna have so much fun!

31
00:05:35.029 --> 00:05:38.788
But I need to see you guys out there.
You can do it! I won!

32
00:05:38.868 --> 00:05:40.108
That was this week's...

33
00:05:40.188 --> 00:05:42.628
We got a disturbance
on elevator 12, plaza level.

34
00:05:42.708 --> 00:05:46.267
...just moments before his
final departure to the Island,

35
00:05:46.347 --> 00:05:49.267
nature's last remaining
pathogen-free zone.

36
00:05:49.347 --> 00:05:51.506
- Lucky guy, huh?
- You can be a winner too.

37
00:05:51.586 --> 00:05:54.506
The next lottery is tonight.

38
00:05:55.826 --> 00:05:59.345
The next lottery is tonight.

39
00:06:01.506 --> 00:06:04.265
- How long have you been here?
- Two years.

40
00:06:05.464 --> 00:06:07.744
- What about you?
- Three.

41
00:06:07.824 --> 00:06:09.703
Three. I've been here seven.

42
00:06:09.783 --> 00:06:13.904
If I do the math, that makes me
the biggest lottery loser in the room.

43
00:06:15.383 --> 00:06:17.981
I'm such a loser.

44
00:06:46.538 --> 00:06:48.777
Sir.

45
00:06:48.817 --> 00:06:50.736
Yeah, you.

46
00:06:52.657 --> 00:06:54.177
Swipe.

47
00:06:55.618 --> 00:06:58.976
Gandu Three Echo, you've been flagged
for public disturbance before.

48
00:06:59.096 --> 00:07:01.935
Yes, I had a very small
emotional outburst, sir.

49
00:07:02.016 --> 00:07:04.496
- Safe to say it's over?
- Yes, very safe.

50
00:07:05.375 --> 00:07:08.454
- I'm feeling much better.
- Well, then, have a pleasant day.

51
00:07:08.494 --> 00:07:11.254
Thank you, you too.
You both have a pleasant day too.

52
00:07:33.291 --> 00:07:34.691
Feel the stretch.

53
00:07:36.289 --> 00:07:37.530
One more breath in.

54
00:07:53.406 --> 00:07:55.087
But I was in that section.

55
00:07:55.167 --> 00:07:56.688
No, I don't understand!

56
00:07:56.768 --> 00:07:59.286
- I tried! I tried to do the best I...
- Listen to me!

57
00:08:00.286 --> 00:08:05.005
Remember, be polite,
pleasant and peaceful.

58
00:08:05.125 --> 00:08:08.764
A healthy person is a happy person.

59
00:08:15.204 --> 00:08:18.963
Lincoln Six Echo, choices are fruit,
oatmeal and any type of bran.

60
00:08:19.003 --> 00:08:20.442
No bacon today?

61
00:08:20.522 --> 00:08:22.644
You got a nutrition flag,
means no bacon.

62
00:08:22.724 --> 00:08:25.122
In that case, two eggs,
over easy, not too runny,

63
00:08:25.202 --> 00:08:26.561
and a side of sausages.

64
00:08:26.641 --> 00:08:29.362
Maybe some French toast
and a little powdered sugar.

65
00:08:30.082 --> 00:08:33.681
You ain't cute and I got no time
for your lip, Six Echo.

66
00:08:33.761 --> 00:08:35.601
Now, what's it gonna be?

67
00:08:35.681 --> 00:08:36.680
Move it.

68
00:08:39.441 --> 00:08:40.681
Surprise me.

69
00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:47.158
Surprise.

70
00:08:48.719 --> 00:08:51.278
Yummy. Next.

71
00:09:02.596 --> 00:09:05.236
Watch and learn.

72
00:09:06.156 --> 00:09:07.755
Next.

73
00:09:07.835 --> 00:09:10.195
Jordan Two Delta.

74
00:09:10.235 --> 00:09:11.755
- Hi, honey.
- Hi.

75
00:09:11.835 --> 00:09:15.194
Choices are powdered eggs,
dried fruit and yogurt.

76
00:09:15.274 --> 00:09:18.034
- Eggs, please.
- OK.

77
00:09:19.633 --> 00:09:22.314
So, where were you the other day?
We missed you.

78
00:09:22.993 --> 00:09:25.912
That's nice of you to say, sweetheart.

79
00:09:26.551 --> 00:09:28.113
Get you anything else?

80
00:09:29.073 --> 00:09:30.313
Maybe a little bacon.

81
00:09:30.913 --> 00:09:32.871
No, it says I shouldn't.

82
00:09:32.911 --> 00:09:36.511
- Go ahead.
- Four, five pieces, please.

83
00:09:38.190 --> 00:09:39.430
Thank you.

84
00:09:41.111 --> 00:09:43.030
Well, good luck.
Gotta run along now.

85
00:09:43.150 --> 00:09:46.230
You're not going.
You gotta stay for dinner.

86
00:09:46.310 --> 00:09:48.869
- I softened her up for you.
- No doubt.

87
00:09:48.949 --> 00:09:51.508
- Back on your diet?
- You kidding? I love this stuff.

88
00:09:51.588 --> 00:09:54.228
Better eat up.
You'll need all your strength tonight.

89
00:09:54.308 --> 00:09:55.469
Is that a challenge?

90
00:09:55.508 --> 00:09:58.028
I promise I'll go easy on you.

91
00:10:00.387 --> 00:10:03.627
Please separate.
Find your seats now.

92
00:10:03.667 --> 00:10:05.547
Yeah.

93
00:10:06.387 --> 00:10:10.985
"'Who wants Sally? ' said Dick.
'I do,' said Jane.

94
00:10:11.065 --> 00:10:13.745
'I cannot find Sally.

95
00:10:13.825 --> 00:10:18.344
Get up, Dick.
Get up and help me find Sally.

96
00:10:18.384 --> 00:10:20.865
Is Sally here?"'

97
00:10:32.623 --> 00:10:35.261
Dr. Merrick will see you now.

98
00:10:39.501 --> 00:10:42.221
What'd you do wrong this time,
tough guy?

99
00:10:45.500 --> 00:10:47.661
Sir?

100
00:10:47.741 --> 00:10:52.338
- You wanted to see me?
- Yes. Please.

101
00:11:00.139 --> 00:11:02.497
Please, sit down.

102
00:11:03.297 --> 00:11:05.858
So, how is Lincoln Six Echo today?

103
00:11:05.898 --> 00:11:08.376
Not so good, I guess.

104
00:11:08.456 --> 00:11:10.336
Why do you say that?

105
00:11:10.416 --> 00:11:13.097
Well, if I'm here,
it means I'm not so good.

106
00:11:13.217 --> 00:11:16.056
That's a rather negative association.

107
00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:20.414
My only job is to see that you're happy,
things are OK with you.

108
00:11:20.454 --> 00:11:21.975
Right.

109
00:11:25.095 --> 00:11:28.014
Your file shows that you've
been interacting regularly

110
00:11:28.094 --> 00:11:29.332
with Jordan Two Delta.

111
00:11:29.372 --> 00:11:33.173
- There's no law against friendship.
- No. No, we encourage it,

112
00:11:33.213 --> 00:11:37.452
but, obviously,
proximity could become a concern.

113
00:11:37.532 --> 00:11:39.413
I know the rules of proximity.

114
00:11:41.651 --> 00:11:44.211
You've been doing quite well
in most other areas.

115
00:11:44.291 --> 00:11:47.170
Proficient at work,
exercising rigorously.

116
00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:50.651
But screening has picked up
some trace levels,

117
00:11:50.771 --> 00:11:54.689
changes in your metabolism,
and you've been having nightmares.

118
00:11:54.770 --> 00:11:57.449
Are you saying there's
something wrong with me?

119
00:11:57.529 --> 00:12:00.008
Why don't you tell me
about your dream?

120
00:12:00.688 --> 00:12:04.888
Well, it's the same dream every time.
I'm on a boat, headed to the Island.

121
00:12:04.968 --> 00:12:08.087
A boat? What kind of boat?

122
00:12:09.567 --> 00:12:10.846
A nice boat.

123
00:12:10.926 --> 00:12:12.406
Draw it for me, would you?

124
00:12:17.726 --> 00:12:21.005
So, you are heading
toward the Island.

125
00:12:21.045 --> 00:12:22.965
What happens then?

126
00:12:23.085 --> 00:12:25.804
- I drown.
- Really?

127
00:12:26.724 --> 00:12:29.644
- Why do you think that is?
- I don't know. You tell me.

128
00:12:29.724 --> 00:12:32.644
- Maybe you're afraid of winning.
- Why would I be afraid?

129
00:12:32.724 --> 00:12:34.483
You tell me.

130
00:12:39.043 --> 00:12:41.322
What's troubling you, Lincoln?

131
00:12:43.441 --> 00:12:45.202
Well, it's...

132
00:12:45.282 --> 00:12:47.360
It's just...

133
00:12:48.121 --> 00:12:50.321
All right.
Tuesday night is tofu night.

134
00:12:50.401 --> 00:12:53.559
And I'm asking myself, who decided
that everyone here likes tofu

135
00:12:53.639 --> 00:12:56.121
in the first place?
And what is tofu, anyway?

136
00:12:56.201 --> 00:12:59.279
And why can't I have bacon?
I line up every morning,

137
00:12:59.319 --> 00:13:02.159
and I'm not allowed any bacon
for my breakfast.

138
00:13:02.199 --> 00:13:04.277
And...
Let's talk about all the white.

139
00:13:04.357 --> 00:13:06.478
Why is everyone
wearing white all the time?

140
00:13:06.518 --> 00:13:10.037
It's impossible to keep clean.
I always get the gray stripe.

141
00:13:10.117 --> 00:13:12.717
I never get any color.
And I hand it in to be cleaned,

142
00:13:12.757 --> 00:13:16.676
and someone cleans it, and folds it
neatly back in my drawer, but who?

143
00:13:16.716 --> 00:13:19.475
Who is that person? I don't know.

144
00:13:19.595 --> 00:13:21.196
I just... I wanna know answers.

145
00:13:21.316 --> 00:13:23.916
And I wish that there was more.

146
00:13:25.075 --> 00:13:26.875
- More?
- Yeah.

147
00:13:26.955 --> 00:13:31.073
More than just waiting
to go to the Island.

148
00:13:33.754 --> 00:13:35.994
Lincoln,

149
00:13:36.074 --> 00:13:38.793
it's your nature
to question things.

150
00:13:38.833 --> 00:13:43.511
But don't you realize how lucky you are?
That you survived the contamination.

151
00:13:43.591 --> 00:13:47.592
That nature has left you
a Garden of Eden to repopulate.

152
00:13:47.672 --> 00:13:50.791
That, Lincoln, is your purpose.

153
00:13:54.470 --> 00:13:58.270
Right. And you?
Aren't you going to the Island too?

154
00:13:58.390 --> 00:14:00.709
No.

155
00:14:00.749 --> 00:14:03.869
My responsibility is to make sure

156
00:14:03.909 --> 00:14:06.149
this facility continues to operate.

157
00:14:06.189 --> 00:14:11.588
That's why people like me,
my staff and supervisors, we...

158
00:14:11.668 --> 00:14:14.228
...we can't win the lottery.

159
00:14:17.147 --> 00:14:18.906
Let me see that.

160
00:14:20.906 --> 00:14:22.666
You draw well.

161
00:14:22.746 --> 00:14:25.586
"Renovatio. "
What does that mean?

162
00:14:25.666 --> 00:14:27.825
I don't know.
It's always in my dream.

163
00:14:30.065 --> 00:14:32.424
I'd like to run some tests
on you, Lincoln.

164
00:14:33.224 --> 00:14:34.584
What sort of tests?

165
00:14:35.424 --> 00:14:37.863
Nice tests.

166
00:14:37.943 --> 00:14:39.223
Come with me.

167
00:14:46.022 --> 00:14:47.742
Take a seat.

168
00:14:52.542 --> 00:14:54.541
OK, let's get you comfortable.

169
00:14:54.620 --> 00:14:56.020
Swing back.

170
00:15:00.579 --> 00:15:03.899
- I thought these were nice tests.
- It's a synaptic brain scan.

171
00:15:03.939 --> 00:15:06.060
Totally harmless.

172
00:15:06.140 --> 00:15:08.979
Don't worry, it's painless.

173
00:15:29.055 --> 00:15:30.535
- It hurts.
- Not really.

174
00:15:30.655 --> 00:15:32.256
- Yeah, it does!
- No, it doesn't.

175
00:15:32.376 --> 00:15:34.574
Yeah, it really, really does!

176
00:15:39.492 --> 00:15:42.574
The micro-sensors
will move along your optic nerve.

177
00:15:42.614 --> 00:15:45.812
They'll be uploading readings
to us over the next 24 hours,

178
00:15:45.892 --> 00:15:48.492
after which,
you'll pass them through your urine.

179
00:15:48.532 --> 00:15:50.572
Now, that might hurt.

180
00:16:01.490 --> 00:16:03.090
Six Echo, you're late.

181
00:16:17.328 --> 00:16:19.207
Jones, you ever get bored doing this?

182
00:16:19.287 --> 00:16:20.487
- Doing what?
- This.

183
00:16:20.527 --> 00:16:23.408
- I never really thought about it.
- I think about it a lot.

184
00:16:23.488 --> 00:16:25.367
- About what?
- This boring job.

185
00:16:25.447 --> 00:16:28.486
- What are we doing here?
- We're feeding the nutrient lines.

186
00:16:28.526 --> 00:16:32.006
We eat food, food's gotta have
vitamins, right? It's good for us.

187
00:16:32.126 --> 00:16:34.646
You don't ever wonder about anything?

188
00:16:34.765 --> 00:16:37.125
Where do these tubes go?

189
00:16:38.285 --> 00:16:39.684
They start there.

190
00:16:39.724 --> 00:16:42.564
And they go... right there.

191
00:16:43.764 --> 00:16:46.522
Hey. Did you get a look
at the new guy?

192
00:16:46.602 --> 00:16:48.563
Seven Foxtrot.

193
00:16:48.643 --> 00:16:52.242
They found another survivor.
They keep finding them.

194
00:16:52.322 --> 00:16:53.922
He'll probably win the lottery.

195
00:16:53.962 --> 00:16:57.120
Straight down, in the hole.
There you go, you try it.

196
00:16:57.200 --> 00:17:00.362
Straight down in the hole.

197
00:17:00.402 --> 00:17:04.080
In the hole.
No, no, no. Put it down.

198
00:17:04.200 --> 00:17:07.441
Did we all look that stupid
when we went through decontamination?

199
00:17:07.521 --> 00:17:11.839
Hey, Mr. Man-With-All-The-Questions,
let me ask you this:

200
00:17:12.639 --> 00:17:14.759
Lottery's supposed
to be random, right?

201
00:17:14.799 --> 00:17:15.839
Right.

202
00:17:15.919 --> 00:17:18.158
What if it's not?
What if it's rigged?

203
00:17:18.879 --> 00:17:19.998
Rigged?

204
00:17:21.397 --> 00:17:23.397
I've been working on this. Here.

205
00:17:23.477 --> 00:17:25.397
Take a look at that.

206
00:17:26.038 --> 00:17:28.957
It charts the last 20 people
that won a spot on the Island.

207
00:17:28.997 --> 00:17:32.196
Excluding, of course, the women,
picked to be breeders.

208
00:17:32.236 --> 00:17:35.076
- What is this?
- I took the first letter in each name.

209
00:17:35.156 --> 00:17:38.115
I assigned it a point value system,
based on the alphabet,

210
00:17:38.235 --> 00:17:40.555
like the last guy,
Starkweather, S equals 15.

211
00:17:40.635 --> 00:17:42.234
Q equals 15, S equals 19.

212
00:17:42.314 --> 00:17:44.315
- Do you see what I'm saying?
- No.

213
00:17:44.355 --> 00:17:47.713
Well, maybe if you would listen to me,
I'm trying to tell you.

214
00:17:47.793 --> 00:17:51.073
You string the numbers together.
You divide it by the amount...

215
00:17:51.113 --> 00:17:54.392
You multiply... You divide it by
the amount of... You divide it...

216
00:17:54.432 --> 00:17:58.752
You divide it by the amount of people,
which is 25, a thousand plus five, 2500.

217
00:17:58.832 --> 00:18:02.432
You know what that spells?
J- O-N-E-S.

218
00:18:03.391 --> 00:18:05.990
- I'm winning the lottery tonight.
- Did you pack?

219
00:18:07.391 --> 00:18:08.791
- No.
- Gentlemen,

220
00:18:09.670 --> 00:18:12.149
I'm gonna go mess with Foxtrot.

221
00:18:12.229 --> 00:18:14.230
There you go. Straight.

222
00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:16.509
Straight down in the hole.

223
00:18:16.589 --> 00:18:18.389
- There you go.
- Straight...

224
00:18:20.270 --> 00:18:22.388
- What? He had something on his... OK.
- Go.

225
00:18:27.507 --> 00:18:29.187
Lima! Are you OK?
What's wrong?

226
00:18:29.267 --> 00:18:32.746
Code 15, we need med-techs stat!
Lima One Alpha.

227
00:18:32.827 --> 00:18:34.467
Let's give her some air, OK?

228
00:18:34.547 --> 00:18:37.066
You're gonna be OK, all right?
Relax and breathe.

229
00:18:37.146 --> 00:18:39.665
Can I get a wheelchair?
It's for Lima One Alpha.

230
00:18:39.745 --> 00:18:43.064
- You OK?
- I think it's time.

231
00:18:45.065 --> 00:18:48.383
Lima, you're going to the Island.

232
00:18:48.503 --> 00:18:51.344
- We're going.
- Oh, you're so lucky.

233
00:18:51.384 --> 00:18:53.224
I hope I see you soon.

234
00:18:55.782 --> 00:19:00.462
Everyone, please follow her out.
Quickly and carefully. Watch the glass.

235
00:19:00.502 --> 00:19:02.543
- Good luck, Lima.
- Thank you.

236
00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:09.101
That's fair. That's real fair.

237
00:19:09.141 --> 00:19:12.460
Ladies, ladies, push back, please.
Gentlemen. Thank you.

238
00:19:16.141 --> 00:19:18.379
Everyone, back to work.

239
00:19:18.419 --> 00:19:20.339
That is so not fair.

240
00:19:21.019 --> 00:19:25.019
Oh, man, I hate this jealousy thing.
It's giving me heart palpitations.

241
00:19:25.099 --> 00:19:27.059
Tech Services.

242
00:19:27.139 --> 00:19:28.858
Computer's down again.

243
00:19:29.737 --> 00:19:31.657
I'm down.
Computer guy's in Sector Six.

244
00:19:31.737 --> 00:19:35.017
I have to deal with this mess.
Take my Tri-Key. Contamination kit.

245
00:19:35.057 --> 00:19:37.097
- Hurry back.
- Absolutely.

246
00:20:04.493 --> 00:20:07.371
- Hey! What are you doing?
- I'm gonna see this guy.

247
00:20:08.531 --> 00:20:12.210
Hey, chief. We got live wires
all over the place here.

248
